 1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Robert de Cauz was born in 1100, in Shelford, Nottinghamshire, England, United Kingdom as the son of Robert de Cauz and Isabel de Ferrers. He had at least 1 daughter with Sibyl Basset. He died in 1168, at the age of 68."},"et":{"1100–1168":"1100–1168","–1177":"–1177","–Male":"Surnud","1125–1185":"1125–1185","1134–1224":"1134–1224","–1168":"–1168","–Female":"Surnud","1224":"1224","1125":"1125","1168":"1168","1134":"1134","1100":"1100","1177":"1177","about 1134":"umbes 1134","1185":"1185","Shelford, Nottinghamshire, England":"Shelford, Nottinghamshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1100–1168":"1100–1168","–1177":"–1177","–Male":"Kuollut","1125–1185":"1125–1185","1134–1224":"1134–1224","–1168":"–1168","–Female":"Kuollut","1224":"1224","1125":"1125","1168":"1168","1134":"1134","1100":"1100","1177":"1177","about 1134":"noin 1134","1185":"1185","Shelford, Nottinghamshire, England":"Shelford, Nottinghamshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1100–1168":"1100–1168","–1177":"–1177","–Male":"Décédé","1125–1185":"1125–1185","1134–1224":"1134–1224","–1168":"–1168","–Female":"Décédée","1224":"1224","1125":"1125","1168":"1168","1134":"1134","1100":"1100","1177":"1177","about 1134":"environ 1134","1185":"1185","Shelford, Nottinghamshire, England":"Shelford, Nottinghamshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Robert de Cauz est né en 1100, à Shelford, Nottinghamshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni, fils de Robert de Cauz et Isabel de Ferrers. Il a eu au moins 1 fille avec Sibyl Basset. Il est décédé en 1168, à l’âge de 68 ans."},"de":{"1100–1168":"1100–1168","–1177":"–1177","–Male":"Verstorben","1125–1185":"1125–1185","1134–1224":"1134–1224","–1168":"–1168","–Female":"Verstorben","1224":"1224","1125":"1